			<ns0:name>j...@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/109636895838879576326/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">I discussed this with kschimpf, mcgrathr and sehr. This change won't simplify any of the validator and we don't think that restricting the input language in this case will give us any advantage, this bug therefore won't be fixed.

The functions in validator.cc (check_loadstore_mask, check_branch_mask, check_data_register_update, check_pc_writes) use the clears_bits function which is now only for BIC, and is implemented as:
  return (imm12.get_modified_immediate(i) &amp; mask) == mask;

The data, code and bundle bytes are passed in to the SfiValidator at construction time, so they're not constants.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-12-10T18:01:33.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-12-10T18:01:33.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates>
